programme.title: Live Checkatrade Trophy
programme.desc: Shrewsbury Town v Yeovil Town (Kick-off 7.45pm). All the action from the semi-final at Montgomery Waters Meadow, as the teams will battle for a place in next month's final at Wembley Stadium, where a meeting with Lincoln City awaits. The Shrews finished as runners-up in this competition in 1996, in what was their sole appearance thus far in the showpiece match, while The Glovers are bidding to reach their first final in this competition

programme.title: Live One-Day International Cricket
programme.sub-title: New Zealand v England: Second ODI.
programme.desc: New Zealand v England. Coverage of the second one-day international of the five-match series, taking place at Bay Oval in Mount Maunganui. England last toured New Zealand for a one-day series back in February 2013, when they emerged 2-1 winners after the three games had taken place. The Black Caps won the first match in Hamilton by three wickets, but the tourists battled back with eight-wicket and five-wicket victories in Napier and Auckland

programme.title: Live ATP Tennis
programme.sub-title: 2018 Dubai Open: Day Three Session One.
programme.desc: The Dubai Duty Free Tennis Championships. Coverage of the third day's play of the tournament from Aviation Club Tennis Centre in Dubai. British star Andy Murray won this event in 2017, defeating Spaniard Fernando Verdasco 6-3, 6-2 to claim what would turn out to be his only title during an injury-plagued season. The Scot is still recovering from recent hip surgery and will not be defending his title here, leaving the door open for a new champion
